Usage: loadViolationReport [-help] -filename <string> [-orient <string>]
                           [-rulemap <string>]
                           -type {Assura Calibre PVS Hercules ICV CDNLitho CDNCMP inShapeLitho CalibreLitho DRV ClockTran CLP VerifyPower}
                           [-xoffset <float>] [-yoffset <float>]

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
-filename <string>          # Violation file (string, required)
-orient <string>            # transform orient: <R0 | R90 | R180 | R270 | MX |
                            # MX90 | MY | MY90> (string, optional)
-rulemap <string>           # specify rule map file for PVS,Calibre
                            # Litho,Calibre report (string, optional)
-type {Assura Calibre PVS Hercules ICV CDNLitho CDNCMP inShapeLitho CalibreLitho DRV ClockTran CLP VerifyPower}
                            # Violation type:
                            # <Assura|Calibre|PVS|Hercules|ICV|CDNLitho|CDNCMP|inShapeLitho|CalibreLitho|DRV|ClockTran|CLP|VerifyPower> (enum, required)
-xoffset <float>            # x offset (float, optional)
-yoffset <float>            # y offset (float, optional)